  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "After using Puppeth for the past few months, I've ran into this issue a few times when I want to deploy to several remote hosts. Puppeth is hardcoded to use the user's default ssh private key `id_rsa`, which forces users like myself to rename ssh keys temporarily so that Puppeth will detect the key and deploy to the host.\r\n \r\nA possible solution might be to have another prompt step during the deploy option where you could input an ssh key name and have Puppeth use that key instead when sshing into the remote host.\r\n\r\nHardcoded private key file line:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/cmd/puppeth/ssh.go#L74\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth version: 1.7.2-stable\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04",
